&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Octopus Legacy is one of the UK&#39;s fastest growing startups, helping over 1 million people plan for and navigate through death - but we&#39;re just getting started. After our founder Sam lost his mum suddenly, we built what the market had never seen: a service that combines estate planning and bereavement support with something genuinely human. Voice notes. Music. Recipes. A legacy that actually means something.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re not competing in this space. We&#39;re redefining it. Backed by Octopus Group, we&#39;re the best positioned business in the market to scale across UK financial services, and we&#39;re moving fast. This role is how we get there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This is a senior, high-impact enterprise sales role. You&#39;ll own the full cycle from pipeline to close, building and converting strategic partnerships with insurers, banks, adviser networks and financial institutions across the UK.You&#39;ll report into the CEO on key deals, and have real influence over how we expand our market share. If you&#39;re a high-performing sales professional looking for a genuine opportunity to build something, rather than maintain a territory someone else built, this is it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be selling with the Octopus Group name behind you. One of the UK&#39;s most recognised and trusted brands, with over 7 million customers and a reputation that opens doors before you&#39;ve said a word. We have the product, the backing and the market timing. We need the person who can go and close it. Octopus already has deep relationships with thousands of financial partners across the UK. This role gets to leverage that network to scale our proposition across UK financial services - and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map the UK financial services landscape and build a targeted pipeline across insurers, banks, adviser networks and wealth managers - then convert them into long-term partnerships that scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage existing relationships across the Octopus Group to open doors faster - then convert them into long-term partnerships that scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get us known. People already know Octopus -&amp;nbsp; this is about showcasing the breadth of services we can offer. Whether that&#39;s speaking at industry events, hosting roundtables or simply being visible across UK wealth, insurance and banking circles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run deals end-to-end. From the first conversation to a signed contract, you&#39;ll navigate complex organisations with multiple stakeholders, align commercial terms, and get ink on paper.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make the numbers do the talking. Build partner-specific business cases showing how our platform drives wealth retention, improves customer experience and supports Consumer Duty obligations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow senior relationships across the sector. You&#39;ll be in rooms with heads of distribution, chief customer officers and board members - the kind of conversations where partnerships are shaped, not just sold.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years selling into UK financial services at an enterprise level. You&#39;ve closed complex, multi-stakeholder deals with insurers, banks or wealth managers and you have the relationships to show for it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You know how these organisations work from the inside - the politics, the buying committees, the commercial pressures. You understand what makes a head of distribution say yes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Naturally curious. You dig into how a partner&#39;s business actually runs before you walk in the room. You understand their customers, their pain points and where we fit.&amp;nbsp;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re Octopus Legacy: one of the fastest growing tech companies in the country, part of the UK’s most exciting and best-trusted group (you may have heard of some of our sister companies…) and we have a mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a path to scale, aiming to become a household name while transforming a long-established industry and helping our customers prepare for, and find support after, death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we can’t do it alone, and that’s why we’re assembling a team of top performers to build with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to be part of something big?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Finance Manager with solid grounding and proven hands-on experience across transactional finance, who’s ready to take real ownership in a fast-scaling business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll sit at the heart of our finance function, ensuring our books are accurately&amp;nbsp; reconciled, and commercially useful as we expand across multiple entities. This is a hands-on role where you’ll own core accounting processes end-to-end - from ledger integrity and reconciliations to management reporting and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll own the integrity of our financial data - improving systems and controls to ensure senior leadership can operate with confidence and clarity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to your development and will support you with funding towards professional qualifications and exams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for the preparation of monthly management accounts, including P&amp;amp;L, balance sheet and cash flow reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage month-end close, reconciliations (bank, expenses, accruals/prepayments), and financial controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and track expenses and departmental budgets, flagging variances and supporting cost control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with external accountants, auditors and vendors to ensure compliance and smooth reporting cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help optimise and improve financial systems, processes and reporting tools as we scale (including automation where possible).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ad-hoc financial analysis to support commercial decisions and operational planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own finance-related aspects of employee onboarding and offboarding (payroll, systems access, documentation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or similar. Working towards (or planning to pursue) a professional accounting qualification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5+ years’ experience in finance, accounting, or a management accounting role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grounding in accounting fundamentals - comfortable reconciling ledgers, reviewing balance sheets, and preparing management accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly detail-oriented, with the discipline to manage high-volume transactional work accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident working across multiple entities and reconciling complex accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel or Google Sheets capability, with hands-on experience using Xero in a multi-entity environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in a fast-paced, scaling environment where processes are evolving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership mindset

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Octopus Legacy is one of the UK&#39;s fastest growing startups, helping over 1 million people plan for and navigate through death - but we&#39;re just getting started. After our founder Sam lost his mum suddenly, we built what the market had never seen: a service that combines estate planning and bereavement support with something genuinely human. Voice notes. Music. Recipes. A legacy that actually means something.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re not competing in this space. We&#39;re redefining it. Backed by Octopus Group, we&#39;re the best positioned business in the market to scale across UK financial services, and we&#39;re moving fast. This role is how we get there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Financial Adviser at Octopus Legacy you’ll be at the heart of one of our most exciting growth areas: delivering holistic, financial planning led advice to clients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have the opportunity to build your own book of clients from day one, with warm leads generated through our unique partnerships with over 100 UK charities, our will writing platform, and our wider Octopus Group network. This isn’t a cold calling role, it’s a genuine opportunity to build a meaningful, long term advisory practice within a high growth business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll sit within a broader financial services function but will have significant autonomy to shape your client relationships and approach. If you’re a driven, client centric adviser who wants to build something meaningful at scale, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Acquisition &amp;amp; Book Building&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create new business opportunities to build your own book of new clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert warm leads generated through our will writing platform, charity partnerships, and Octopus Group network into long term client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a strong pipeline of prospects, tracking activity and progress through our CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a referral network over time as your client base grows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Planning &amp;amp; Advice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide holistic financial advice with a financial planning led approach, understanding each client’s unique circumstances, goals, and aspirations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help clients chart the course to live the lives they dream of, from retirement planning and investment management through to estate planning and legacy considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce clear, compliant suitability reports and financial plans tailored to each client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with regulatory requirements, product developments, and financial planning best practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Relationships &amp;amp; Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver an exceptional client service experience at every touchpoint, building multi generational relationships with both mass affluent and high net worth clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular client reviews to ensure advice remains appropriate and relevant as circumstances evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work sensitively and empathetically with clients around life events including bereavement, serious illness and estate planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all client interactions and records meet FCA compliance and data protection requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our will writing, legal, and partnerships teams to ensure a seamless client experience across the Octopus Legacy product suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The General Manager will work closely with the CEO to lead Octopus Legacy towards its ambition of becoming the UK’s defining brand in estate planning and support after loss. Estate Planning is the core engine of the business - driving revenue, customer growth, brand trust, and long-term value creation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role carries full end-to-end accountability for the unit’s performance, growth and transformation. The GM will own strategy, commercial performance, operational delivery, people leadership, and customer outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beyond running the business, this role will lead a critical evolution: transitioning Estate Planning from a predominantly service-led model to a scalable, technology-enabled platform that delivers exceptional customer outcomes and margin strength. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will guide the business through a period of rapid growth and increasing complexity, stabilising and scaling operations, embedding systems and processes for efficiency, and taking full P&amp;amp;L ownership - all while working closely with the founder and executive team to shape the future direction of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and deliver a clear short and long-term strategy for the Estate Planning business that directly supports Octopus Legacy’s broader ambition and growth plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all aspects of the business unit, including revenue, service delivery, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of commercial and operational performance, translating strategy into clear KPIs, measurable outcomes, and disciplined execution across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing and New Business to drive viral growth, strengthen the brand, and scale lead generation and conversion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product and Technology to prioritise and accelerate initiatives that improve systems, tooling, and workflows, driving operational efficiency and scalability. Build a best-in-class technology platform connecting our products and customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage financial resources, including budgeting, forecasting, and reporting to ensure sustainable growth and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take complex, ambiguous problems and opportunities from definition through to delivery, working ‘hands-on’ across teams to remove blockers, improve ways of working, and embed outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain rigorous compliance with all legal and regulatory requirements, embedding robust quality assurance and risk management processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with key internal and external stakeholders — including customers, partners and industry bodies — to strengthen our market position and reputation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and strengthen our high-performance, customer-first culture during rapid scale (c.150 → 300 team size), reinforcing high standards of accountability, behaviour and results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attract, recruit, develop and retain an exceptional team, building succession depth for critical roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate market, regulatory and operational risks, and respond with structured, forward-looking action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the organisational scaffolding required for a scaling business unit — formal enough to ensure clarity and control, but lean enough to maintain momentum and entrepreneurial pace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the CEO, Board, and HoF team as a trusted senior operator, aligning Estate Planning priorities with company direction while helping to shape that direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success looks like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful introduction of new products or service enhancements measured by time-to-market

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Graduate Sales Associate at Octopus Legacy, you&#39;ll begin your career guiding people through one of the hardest moments of their lives - and helping them feel calm, supported and confident about the practical steps that follow a death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a sales and customer service role at heart, and the perfect launchpad for an ambitious graduate. You&#39;ll learn how to be the first voice our customers hear after a bereavement, the trusted person who explains how we can take the weight of probate and estate administration off their shoulders, and the problem-solver who helps them choose the service that&#39;s genuinely right for them. You&#39;ll develop the ability to blend empathy with commercial awareness: supporting people through grief while guiding them to the right decision and working towards your targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&#39;t need any prior experience. If you&#39;ve got the drive to build a career in sales and the empathy to handle sensitive conversations, we&#39;ll teach you everything else - including everything you need to know about probate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to be honest - it won&#39;t always be easy. You&#39;ll be speaking to people at the most difficult and emotional moments in their lives, often when they need guidance and reassurance the most. It takes resilience, calm under pressure, and the ability to stay warm and clear even when conversations are tough. But if you&#39;re someone who finds purpose in helping people when it matters most - and you thrive in a fast-paced, target-driven environment - this role can be an incredibly rewarding place to start.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From day one you&#39;ll be given real ownership, proper training, and the freedom to be human - no rigid scripts, no robotic call targets. As part of our founding probate sales team, you&#39;ll join at a pivotal time, with genuine room to grow into more senior roles as you develop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are simple: Customer-First. Work hard. Stay optimistic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn to be the first point of contact for customers after a death via phone, email, and chat — guiding them with clarity, warmth, and confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand each customer&#39;s situation and recommend the right probate and estate administration services for what they&#39;re going through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead consultations and quote calls (with full training and support), explain options clearly, and help customers make a confident, informed decision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the customer journey from first enquiry through to instructing the service, ensuring a seamless experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work towards personal and team sales targets for engagement, conversion, and customer satisfaction, while always keeping support quality first.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep accurate and confidential customer records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share fresh ideas to improve processes, resources, and the overall customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across teams and bring energy, initiative, and a problem-solving mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A recent graduate (or early-career candidate) eager to build a career in sales and customer success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A compassionate communicator who builds trust easily - especially when conversations are tough.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motivated by targets and commercially curious, with a genuine desire to help customers choose what&#39;s right for them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resilient and adaptable, able to stay calm in high-pressure and emotional situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised, attentive to detail, and comfortable managing multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive and solutions-focused, always thinki

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re Octopus Legacy: one of the fastest growing tech companies in the country, part of the UK&#39;s most exciting and best-trusted group (you may have heard of some of our sister companies…) and we have a mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re on a path to scale, aiming to become a household name while transforming a long-established industry and helping our customers prepare for, and find support after, death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we can&#39;t do it alone, and that&#39;s why we&#39;re assembling a team of top performers to build with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to be part of something big?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Probate Legal Assistant at Octopus Legacy, you&#39;ll sit at the heart of our probate team - supporting families through the practical, legal steps that follow a death, and making sure every case runs smoothly from the very first conversation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work side by side with our Probate Case Managers, learning the ins and outs of probate applications and estate administration as you go. You&#39;ll be speaking to customers who are bereaved, so warmth, clarity and care matter as much as the admin itself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&#39;t need a legal background. If you&#39;re organised, empathetic, and genuinely good with people, we&#39;ll teach you everything you need to know about probate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to be honest - it won&#39;t always be easy. You&#39;ll be speaking to people at one of the hardest moments of their lives. It takes patience, attention to detail, and the ability to stay calm and kind when things get emotional or busy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But if you find purpose in helping people when it matters most - and you like the idea of building your career in a fast-growing, supportive team - this role can be genuinely rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our growing probate team, you&#39;ll join at a pivotal time, helping us shape the way we work and deliver the best possible experience for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are simple: Customer-First. Work hard. Stay optimistic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle inbound &amp;amp; outbound calls, share updates, and support customers with warmth and confidence, especially in sensitive moments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare correspondence, chase information, and manage legal forms accurately and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce documents, manage busy diaries, and keep our filing and case records organised and up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Case Managers across the full life of a case, helping everything run seamlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep customer records accurate and confidential at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share insights and ideas to improve our processes, resources, and the overall customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across teams to drive efficiency and elevate service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A compassionate communicator who builds trust easily - especially when conversations are tough.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised and detail-focused, comfortable working from a task list and juggling multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-first, with the emotional intelligence to support people through bereavement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident with everyday tech and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong written and verbal communicator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive and solutions-focused, always thinking about how to make things better.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team player who leads with kindness and genuinely cares about doing meaningful work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A legal background is a bonus, not a requirement - we&#39;ll train you on the rest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
