&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re Octopus Legacy: one of the fastest growing tech companies in the country, part of the UK’s most exciting and best-trusted group (you may have heard of some of our sister companies…) and we have a mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a path to scale, aiming to become a household name while transforming a long-established industry and helping our customers prepare for, and find support after, death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we can’t do it alone, and that’s why we’re assembling a team of top performers to build with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to be part of something big?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dedicated Private Client Solicitor to join our growing team. You will be responsible for crafting bespoke wills, providing IHT guidance, and advising on, establishing and administering trusts for clients who require tailored solutions that accurately reflect their wishes regarding the distribution of their assets. This role involves working closely with clients to understand their unique circumstances, including complex family structures, business ownership, and other considerations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need a strong understanding of trusts, inheritance tax and estate planning, as well as excellent communication skills to effectively advise clients and ensure their wishes are properly documented. Your expertise in trusts will allow you to provide strategic advice on wealth preservation, inheritance tax planning, and asset protection. Experience in probate and estate administration is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with clients to understand their estate planning needs and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse complex family and financial situations to determine appropriate estate planning and trust strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft wills, trusts (including discretionary, life interest, and bare trusts), and other estate planning documents tailored to each client&#39;s individual circumstances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expert guidance on the creation, administration, and taxation of trusts, ensuring compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise clients on the implications of trust structures for asset protection, succession planning, and tax efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and revise existing wills, trusts, and estate planning documents as necessary to accommodate changes in clients&#39; circumstances or the law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with financial advisors, and other professionals to develop comprehensive estate and trust planning solutions for clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle the administration of trusts, ensuring proper management and distribution of assets in line with settlors’ intentions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain confidentiality and discretion when handling sensitive client information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of industry trends and best practices in estate planning and trust law to enhance service delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solicitor with a minimum of 3+ years PQE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in drafting and advising on complex wills, trusts, and estate structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in trust administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full TEP membership (preferable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re Octopus Legacy: one of the fastest growing tech companies in the country, part of the UK’s most exciting and best-trusted group (you may have heard of some of our sister companies…) and we have a mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a path to scale, aiming to become a household name while transforming a long-established industry and helping our customers prepare for, and find support after, death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we can’t do it alone, and that’s why we’re assembling a team of top performers to build with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to be part of something big?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a mission to revolutionise Probate and Estate Planning by building a more human, tech-enabled legal experience - and we’re looking for a hands-on, passionate Private Client Solicitor to join us on the journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be joining the legal arm of Octopus Legacy, working at the heart of our Probate service. From day one, you’ll take ownership of a diverse caseload, primarily focused on probate and estate administration, with the opportunity to expand into trusts and estate planning over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity for an experienced Private Client Solicitor ready to leave the traditional law firm model behind. You’ll join our expanding legal team to introduce fresh ideas, streamline processes, and challenge the status quo. In doing so, you’ll play a key role in shaping innovative ways of delivering probate services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally between Octopus Legacy and our subsidiary Octopus Legal Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a portfolio of probate matters, demonstrating expertise in complex grant-only and administration cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key client contact from the outset, leading initial calls and fostering trust throughout the process through clear and empathetic communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support estate planning work, including complex wills, with opportunities to work on trusts where relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help us build and refine scalable legal processes - contributing to templates, resources, and the evolution of how we do things.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across the wider Octopus Legacy and Octopus Legal Services teams, sharing insights and working together to provide a seamless client journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be open to ad hoc projects and responsibilities that come with being part of a fast-moving, high-growth team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A qualified Private Client Solicitor focused on Probate with 3+ years PQE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised and proactive, with a calm, confident approach to managing your workload and juggling priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
